    <h1 id="overview">Choosing a valuation method</h1>
    <h2>Deciding which Net Operating Income period to capitalize</h2>
    <br>
    <p>
      The Net Realizable Reversionary Value is a function of the NOI and the
      Reversionary Capitalization Rate, however which NOI period should be
      capitalized?
    </p>
    <figure>
      <div class="flex flex-col gap-6">
        <math>
          <mi>Reversionary Value</mi>
          <mpadded lspace="0.3em" width="2em">
            <mo>=</mo>
          </mpadded>
          <mfrac>
            <mpadded height="1.2em" voffset="0.2em">
              <mi>Net Operating Income</mi>
            </mpadded>
            <mpadded height="1.1em">
              <mi>Reversionary Capitalization Rate</mi>
            </mpadded>
          </mfrac>
        </math>
      </div>
    </figure>
    <p>
      ReturnSuite users have three choices of NOI periods to capitalize, all of
      which are based on the End Date of the Analysis Period. The choices are:
    </p>
    <ol class="list-decimal pl-8 text-gray-800 text-base pb-2 leading-8">
      <li><b>Forward 12-Months</b> - the total forecasted NOI in the year after the valuation date (most common method),</li>
      <li><b>Trailing 12-Months</b> - the total NOI in the year leading up to the valuation date , or</li>
      <li><b>Average 24-Months</b> - the one-year average NOI for 12 months before and after the valuation date.</li>
    </ol>
    <figure>
      <figcaption>[Insert ReturnSuite GIF]</figcaption>
    </figure>
    <hr class="mt-2 mb-6 border-gray-300">
